cs.CR, cs.WEB, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper primarily focuses on the effectiveness and efficiency of ad-blocking filters, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). However, it also touches upon web technologies (cs.WEB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of analyzing website content and detecting ad-blocking evasion techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of ad-blocking on user experience and proposes optimizations for mobile devices, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and systems and networking (cs.SI).
